Package ie.gmit.dip

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    MapComparable
    Used to ensure that the two Maps are merged and compared separately.
    Menuable
    Interface which ensures that the displaying of options and the user selection are separated.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CalculateResult
    Calculates the result of a comparison to be displayed elsewhere.
    CompareFiles
    Controls the flow of methods and classes called in order to compare the files correctly.
    ComparisonTypeSelection
    The user inputs the type of comparison they would like to use, e.g.
    CosineComparisonHashMaps
    Compares two hash maps using a TreeSet of integers using cosine comparison.
    CosineComparisonStringMaps
    Compares two hash maps using a TreeSet of String using cosine comparison.
    DisplayAnswer
    Calculation results passed in and displayed to the user.
    DisplayLoadingScreen
    Contains all the loading screens for the program.
    FileComparisonManager
    Contains the information for the query and search files in addition to the variables for comparison.
    FileDividor
    Incoming file is parsed and divided according to user input stored in the FileInfoManager.
    FileInfo
    Class containing file paths for the files that are going to be compared.
    HashFileHandler
    Used for the executorService to return an integer to integer Map through the FileDividor class.
    InputFilesSelection
    Asks the user to input the file paths for the query and search files.
    LineDivisionInfo
    Contains the information for the way in which the files will be divided for comparison.
    MainMenu
    Main menu where the user is guided through the selection process to then start comparing the text files.
    MapInfo
    Contains the information for the maps from search key to number of times the key appears in a text.
    MapInfoManager
    Object containing two Maps from either String or Integer to Integer.
    PopulateMap
    Populates a HashMap with the key as either a String or integer from the text and maps it to an integer being the number of times the key appears in the text.
    Runner
    Starting point for the threaded cosine based text comparison program.
    StringFileHandler
    Used for the executorService to return an string to integer Map through the FileDividor class.
    TextDivisionSelection
    User inserts their choice for the way in which the text file is divided for subsequent comparison.
    Verification
    Class containing all of the verification methods used in the program.
